content.text: When "0" and "1" are written on paper: - Touching horizontally: observed as "01" - Touching vertically: observed as "10" - Separated: observed as "0 1" or "0∠1" - At critical distance: may produce AlienatedNumber("01") or collapse to Ø This simple observation reveals that mathematical identity is inseparable from spatial configuration
